                "line": "\n"
            },
            {
                "line": "Fleming himself cautioned that overuse of antibiotics could lead to resistant bacteria, a warning that has proved remarkably prescient. Today, antimicrobial resistance is recognised by the World Health Organisation as one of the greatest threats to global public health, driven in part by the widespread and often unnecessary prescription of antibiotics in both human medicine and agriculture."
